content:
Activity reports are useful for gathering information about open activities, completed activities, multi-person events, or pending approval requests. Standard activity reports allow you to select the date range and status of the activities you want included.

Standard Reports:
* Choose the HTML Email Status report if you have HTML email tracking enabled.
* Choose the Events with Invitees report to include only multi-person events in your report.
* The My Delegated Approval Requests report lists all the approval requests for which you're the approval proxy.

Special Features of Activity Reports:

* Consider the following when running activity reports:
	+ Standard Reports
	+ Report Types (using report builder to create custom activity reports)
	+ Tips for Activity Reports (setting search criteria, archived activities, and private contacts)

Report Filters:

* My Activities—Shows activities that you own.
* My Delegated Activities—Shows activities that you created but that someone else owns.
* My Team's Activities—Shows activities owned by users who report to you in the role hierarchy.
* All Activities—Shows all activities that you can view, as determined by your sharing model.

Note: Some filters may not be visible depending on your edition.
title: Understanding Salesforce Activity Reports
